<p>FOR THE PRIME MINISTER PERSONAL HIMSELF</p>

<p>Reference my telegram en clair B 84. [1] Statement has caused grave concern here on grounds: (1) disclosure secret D W information (2) â€˜Large proportionâ€™ of inaccuracy. [2]</p>

<p>With regard to (1) although publicity given in French [3] communiques nothing has been said here as proposed joint French and British communique would be made at appropriate moment framed to obviate suggestion British desertion of the French.</p>

<p>With regard to (2) forty thousand out of 200,000 not large proportion but if believed by Germans might stimulate them to intensify attacks; also tendency to raise false hopes among relatives of members of B.E.F.</p>

<p>BRUCE</p>

